I"7<p>Disclaimer: Great care should be taken when altering the behavior of the cooling fans if you overheat your Mac for an extended period you will destroy it! As such do this at your own risk and if you need to consult an expert.</p>

<p>That being said this tip can really help extend the working life of your Mac.</p>

<p>One of the most common hardware failures on all computers not just Macs is continued over heating of the internal components especially the GPU (graphics card), and traditional HDD modules (hard drives with moving parts) .</p>

<p>The following shows the internal temperatures on an iMac 27 inch, Mid 2011 with two external displays connected via the Thunderbolt ports. The room temperature is 25 degrees Celsius (77 degrees Fahrenheit). The iMac has been running for about 45 minutes from cold.</p>
